7. Use Container Widget with height and width property in Flutter App Development

✅ Explanation (Exam-Oriented)

The Container widget in Flutter uses height and width properties to define its size.
These properties help in controlling the layout and dimensions of UI elements.

height → sets vertical size
width → sets horizontal size

//main code

import 'package:flutter/material.dart';

void main() {
  runApp(MyApp());
}

class MyApp extends StatelessWidget {
  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return MaterialApp(
      home: ContainerSizeExample(),
    );
  }
}

class ContainerSizeExample extends StatelessWidget {
  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return Scaffold(
      appBar: AppBar(
        title: Text("Container Height & Width"),
      ),
      body: Center(
        child: Container(
          height: 150,
          width: 250,
          color: Colors.green,
          child: Center(
            child: Text(
              "Fixed Size Box",
              style: TextStyle(color: Colors.white, fontSize: 18),
            ),
          ),
        ),
      ),
    );
  }
}